        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 4:27PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 426 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Crystal Hill, or near Halifax, moving south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
South Boston...
Halifax...
Clover...
Scottsburg...
Crystal Hill...
Dryburg...
and John H Kerr Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Locally heavy rain will quickly reduce visibility and result in
ponding of water on roadways, standing water in low lying areas, and
minor flooding of creeks, streams, and areas of poor drainage.
Drivers are urged to slow down and use extra caution to avoid
hydroplaning.</instruction>
